&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chief Cardiac Physiologist -&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(Band 7) - Cardiology – Ealing Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;This role is designed for the Chief Cardiac Physiologist with a broad based knowledge of cardiology investigations within a busy and reactive department. The position is to lead in a technical/clinical area and be responsible for the teaching, training and supervision of Cardiac Physiologist with less experienced staff.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will be required to have: &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- BSc (Hon) in Clinical Physiology or equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- BSE or HRUK / IBHRE accredited or equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Advance knowledge and experience in angiography, PCI’s and advanced angiography techniques and or Advance knowledge and experience in Echo/TOE/Stress Echo. A sound understanding of basic pacemaker implants would be advantageous. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Ealing Hospital is part of The London North West University Trust integrated with Northwick Park and Central Middlesex Hospital. The Cardiology unit at Ealing Hospital is a busy department performing a wide range of diagnostic investigations both invasive and non-invasive. At NWP hospital they have opened a new second state of the art catheter lab, performing primary PCI’s, advanced techniques as well as complex and routine pacemaker implants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We encourage physiologists to be specialist practitioners in multiple areas where training will be given.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;** Please apply for this position if you have not done so within the last 6 months **&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameNatasha GulbenkianTelephone number07384900675Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For enquiries, please contact Natasha Gulbenkian, Principal Cardiac Physiologist – Natasha.gulbenkian@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
